snippet: The Chicago Transit Authority said an empty commuter train crashed into a train carrying passengers in Forest Park on Monday, injuring as many as four dozen people.
abstract: Chicago Transit Authority says empty commuter train crashed into another train stopped at station in Forest Park during morning rush, injuring as many as four dozen passengers.
lead_paragraph: The Chicago Transit Authority said an empty commuter train crashed into a train carrying passengers in Forest Park on Monday, injuring as many as four dozen people.

headline.main: Illinois: Commuter Trains Collide, Injuring Dozens
